4. Strategic Implementation Tips
Chunking Strategy: Do not just split by page. Split by sub-headings (e.g., "We Face Intense Competition," "Our International Operations"). This ensures that when a user asks about "International Risks," the retrieved chunk contains the full list of relevant points.
Metadata Tagging: When ingesting the PDF into your vector database, add metadata tags like section="Risk Factors", topic="International", or year="2019". This allows you to implement hybrid search (keyword + semantic) later if needed.
Evaluation Test Set: Create a small set of "Golden Questions" based on the text to test your system before submission.
Q: "What percentage of revenue comes from Q4?" -> A: "Approximately 31% in 2019."
Q: "Who is the CEO of AWS?" -> A: "Andrew R. Jassy."
Q: "What are the risks regarding China?" -> A: (Must cite regulatory licensing and foreign ownership restrictions mentioned in Item 1A).
By treating this 10-K not just as a text file but as a structured dataset requiring careful preprocessing, you directly address the "Data & AI Depth" criteria of the assignment.